T49988.00    [RISK-INCOME-1]                                Survey Year: 2014
  PRIMARY VARIABLE

             CHOOSING FIRST JOB OR SECOND JOB
 
Suppose that you are the only income earner in the family, and that you have to 
choose between two new jobs. The first job would guarantee your current total 
family income for life. The second job is possibly better paying, but the income
is also less certain. There is a 50-50 chance the second job would increase your
total lifetime income by 20 percent and a 50-50 change that is would cut it by 
10 percent.
 
Which job would you take: the first job or the second job?
 
